  "response_text": "The commercial is in black and white and begins in a staged jewelry-shop setting. A clean-cut adult man with dark hair stands facing forward, dressed formally in a dark suit jacket, white shirt, bow tie, and pocket square. He smiles as he speaks. To his left is a display counter filled with small watch or jewelry items, arranged in rows with little signs or cards. Behind him are shelves holding boxes and display pieces, and a leafy plant sits near the counter, giving the set a neat retail-showroom feel.\n\nThe presenter remains beside the display counter, addressing the viewer directly. He shifts his posture slightly and gestures with one hand toward the merchandise. After a few moments he reaches to the counter and lifts a small open presentation case. He brings it up to chest height and holds it with both hands, angling it forward so the contents face the viewer.\n\nThe view changes to a close look at the open case. Inside is a satin-lined watch box with the word “BULOVA” printed on the inner cushion, and “BULOVA” also appears across the front edge of the case. Resting inside is a delicate ladies’ wristwatch. The watch has a small bright face and a narrow metal bracelet. A hand reaches down from above, pinches the watch carefully by the bracelet, and lifts it out of the box.\n\nThe watch is then held suspended in front of a plain background. It dangles from the fingers, with its small face catching the light. Another hand comes up behind it, palm and fingers forming a backdrop so the watch can be seen more clearly. The watch is positioned upright against the hand. Its face is small and light-toned, framed by an ornate, decorative case. The bracelet is narrow and segmented, with small metal sections above and below the face.\n\nA closer view shows the watch held against the fingers. The face has dark hour markers and dark hands, with a rounded or oval decorative case around it. A fingertip points to the lower part of the bracelet, drawing attent